comment_displayed: I appreciate your comments. They are valid. However, lets put things in historical perspective. Eastern Europe was occupied by the Soviets for fifty years after The Great Patriotic War. Do you think such people forget such things? Of course not. So it is natural for those countries that the Soviets occupied to want to defend themselves. Admittedly the US generated a coup in Ukraine, which the Russians responded by occupying the Russian speaking portions of Ukraine. The same argument was made by Hitler when he took over Austrian and the Sudetenland in the Czech Republic. There are Russian speaking people in the Baltic Countries and Eastern Europe. Is Russia going to use the same argument to liberate them? So the consequence is that these countries are preparing against a Russian invasion. Russia says they are building defenses on their border. These countries are saying, No, we are building defenses on OUR borders. Dont forget it wasnt that long ago that the Russians shot down the plane full of the Polish government officials. People dont forget these things. So the actions of Russia in Ukraine and their support for rogue regimes like Syria, Iran, Yemen, Hezbollah, et cetera doesnt make them look like they are friends to the rest of the world. In short, Russia is suffering for the consequences of the current and previous actions. They have been the wolves not the lambs so they should stop acting like victims. Likewise, China declaring that 3/4 ths of the South China Sea is like the United States claiming sovereignty in the Pacific Ocean to Hawaii. Its a ridiculous argument designed only to flex their own power. Then the Chinese buy oil from Iran, sign a pack with Pakistan, which only aggravates India. India very well may be the future of Asia in the future. The Chinese have a debt to income ratio of 3 to 1l they have built a bunch of cities of 10 million people where nobody lives; there population is aging; and they have a shortage of women due to their one child policy. Of course, these two countries are trying to knock the US off their perch. But what they dont see is that the rest of the world is not comfortable with the actions of Russia and China -- effectively governments run by dictators. So whose side do you think the rest of the countries of the world will side with?
